05:50.464 --> 05:53.686
the technical and data analysis support for realignment of district

05:53.718 --> 05:57.900
boundaries. That process will continue through September of 2022.

05:58.430 --> 06:01.770
Staff is creating a team to provide demographic and population

06:01.850 --> 06:05.754
projections for the city of Houston. Up until now, we've not projected

06:05.802 --> 06:09.802
population, we've simply identified what other agencies

06:09.866 --> 06:13.346
have calculated. So projections will be new for us and

06:13.368 --> 06:17.154
for the city, and it will support other city departments in right sizing their

06:17.192 --> 06:20.786
service operations. Our transportation planners have so

06:20.808 --> 06:24.114
many projects, it's hard to keep up, but I hope you had a chance

06:24.152 --> 06:27.718
to listen to the Mayor's State of Mobility address this afternoon. A transcript and a

06:27.724 --> 06:31.062
video is going to be available later today, but in addition to that,

06:31.116 --> 06:33.430
we have increased coordination with Metro,

06:33.930 --> 06:37.494
specifically about the University Corridor and the Intercatty Bus Rapid

06:37.542 --> 06:40.714
Transit lines. We're also receiving frequent requests for

06:40.752 --> 06:44.650
connectivity studies in various council districts and

06:44.720 --> 06:48.134
Houston is the largest city in the United States without a map designating

06:48.182 --> 06:52.362
truck routes, which means that freight travel often cuts through residential neighborhoods.

06:52.426 --> 06:55.870
So in the coming year, the citywide Freight Map project

06:55.940 --> 06:59.374
will coordinate with council members and neighborhoods to secure some relief for

06:59.412 --> 07:02.558
them. And when it comes to increasing Houstonian's

07:02.574 --> 07:06.174
equity, we're still collaborating with the Kinder Institute on the Equity

07:06.222 --> 07:10.114
Indicators project to provide transparency, accountability and

07:10.152 --> 07:13.626
to refine operations for all city departments to increase

07:13.678 --> 07:17.574
equity across our city. The initial analysis is nearly completed but

07:17.612 --> 07:21.314
and the program will require ongoing management and measure to measure

07:21.362 --> 07:23.190
success in closing the gaps.

07:24.650 --> 07:28.374
Our ongoing work with neighborhood resiliency plans address storm recovery,

07:28.422 --> 07:32.406
watershed boundaries and other challenges like climate adaption, risk reduction,

07:32.518 --> 07:36.342
economic development, infrastructure modernization and social empowerment.

07:36.486 --> 07:40.042
Currently there are three plans to be completed by 2023, with another

07:40.096 --> 07:43.326
three to be completed afterward. And staff is developing a

07:43.348 --> 07:46.702
replicable framework for other neighborhoods to follow in creating their own

07:46.756 --> 07:49.998
resiliency plans. And our minimum lot size and

07:50.004 --> 07:53.806
minimum building line programs, which are so popular for neighborhoods, are reaching

07:53.838 --> 07:56.994
their 20 year threshold, which means

07:57.032 --> 08:00.962
that we're creating significant increase in we're getting requests for

08:01.016 --> 08:04.454
significant increase in renewals on top of the average projected new

08:04.492 --> 08:07.430
applications. And finally,

08:07.580 --> 08:10.070
historic preservation team we've created.

08:10.410 --> 08:14.006
Two new historic districts have been petitioned and we

08:14.028 --> 08:17.966
are working with the Economic Development Office for review and administration

08:18.018 --> 08:22.010
of the historic Site tax exemption program, which is growing in popularity.

08:22.910 --> 08:26.234
We expect conservation districts to presented to city Council within

08:26.272 --> 08:29.846
the next few months. A conservation district for Independence Heights will

08:29.888 --> 08:33.466
probably follow shortly thereafter. We see conservation districts

08:33.498 --> 08:37.018
as providing neighborhoods another tool for protecting their character.

08:37.194 --> 08:40.782
So I'm excited about all the partnerships we've forged and look forward

08:40.836 --> 08:43.120
to working with you on another collaborative year.

08:43.490 --> 08:46.626
